1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper focuses on the design of hybrid precoding and diversity combining in millimeter wave MIMO systems, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): Millimeter wave MIMO systems are widely used in wireless communication networks, and the proposed schemes in this paper can potentially improve the performance of such networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The design of hybrid precoding and diversity combining involves system optimization and control, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): Millimeter wave MIMO systems are also used in multimedia applications, such as virtual reality and augmented reality, which may require low latency and high data rates. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language): Although less likely, this paper involves some sparse reconstruction techniques, which may be relevant to natural language processing and other computational linguistics applications.
